{"tid":108061,"cid":6,"subCid":0,"title":"ZACH LAVINE斷韌帶收咧","createTime":"2017-02-05T02:30:56.000Z","updateTime":"2017-02-05T05:28:28.000Z","uid":60794,"like":0,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"3af410cce021dec59a2be3d90c9560afdc5a8817","tid":108061,"uid":60794,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-05T02:30:56.000Z","msg":"Zach LaVine out for the rest of the season with torn ACL<br />\nFebruary 4, 2017 by Timberwolves PR<br />\n<br />\nMinneapolis/St. Paul &ndash; The Minnesota Timberwolves today announced that an MRI (Magnetic Resonance Imaging) taken this morning at Mayo Clinic by Team Orthopedic Surgeon Dr. Diane Dahm revealed that Wolves guard Zach LaVine has a torn ACL (Anterior Cruciate Ligament) in his left knee. LaVine, who will have surgery at a to-be-determined date, will miss the remainder of the season. Further updates as to LaVine&rsquo;s progress will be issued when more information becomes available.<br />\n<br />\nThe injury occurred during last night&rsquo;s 116-108 loss to the Detroit Pistons.<br />\n<br />\nIn 47 games this season, LaVine averaged 18.9 points, 3.4 rebounds and 3.0 assists in 37.2 minutes per game. In his third NBA season, LaVine holds career averages of 13.7 points, 2.9 rebounds and 3.2 assists in 206 games.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/23.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/23.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/23.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a37462b760521c1fbeede85e74160bd82290e885","tid":108061,"uid":78574,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-05T02:32:08.000Z","msg":"唔玩入樽賽想專心打波先黎傷<img src=\"/assets/faces/lomoji/23.png\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0d7cad3ca828f6fe66725f7024075665dc05fb34","tid":108061,"uid":63675,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-02-05T02:34:45.000Z","msg":"fuck me<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/frown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"72cac7